ì@ade8dedf8ae8f894f0ccdf14dbe58f1b9c7ce54ab9883fe5bb2e10e44790a8f0ÖoTitle: This week in Nu #15
Path: This week in Nu #15
Content:
Major internals work this week as multiple refactorings land.
sebastian-xyz added the new 
``range``
 command (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1045] #1045
)
thegedge simplified the pipeline execution code (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1039] #1039
)
wycats begun the process of reorganizing the codebase to use subcrates for better code modularity (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1046] #1046
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1044] #1044
)
jonathandturner continued extracting plugins into subcrates and organizing commands/plugins for maximal portability (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1058] #1058
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1055] #1055
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1054] #1054
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1052] #1052
)
jonathandturner also added a new type to represent a string with a carriage return, fixing an issue when stream large amounts of text (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1047] #1047
)
jonathandturner shipped the 0.6.1 release with a fix for the starship prompt (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1035] #1035
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1029] #1029
)
andrasio updated 
``embed``
 to more naturally embed a single column (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1049] #1049
)
tchak and sebastian-xyz added more command documentation (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1041] #1041
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1032] #1032
)
